history.content:
They’re used as placeholders for discussion sections and for many lab sections for CS and EE classes.  The reasoning behind this was that before, if you wanted to switch to a different section, you literally had to drop the class and re-add the class which for classes that are full is impossible to re-add.

Later on, right before class starts, there usually will an announcement to sign up for sections via SignupGenius or some other software at a specific date and time.  Some classes, like CS70 or EE16A/B, you can go to any discussion section and sign up.  Do note that for EE16A/B you do need to register for the lab via CalCentral.
